data.meta_description: Day.js supports time zone via the [Internationalization API](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl) in [supported environments](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/DateTimeFormat#Browser_compatibility). data.text:
Day.js supports time zone via the Internationalization API in supported environments. By using the native API, no extra bytes of timezone data need to be included in code bundle.

The list of all time zone names can be found in the IANA database.

For legacy or unsupported environments, please use a proper polyfill.

This requires the Timezone plugin to work
